The cabinet shall review and shall approve or deny the environmental covenant, or request additional information as part of its review of a corrective action plan submitted pursuant to KRS 224.1-400, 224.1-405, 224.46-530 and 224.1-450 to 224.1-465. The cabinet shall review the environmental covenant and determine whether:
The real property is eligible for an environmental covenant under KRS 224.80-100 to 224.80-210;
The environmental covenant is complete;
The environmental covenant is protective of human health, safety, and the environment under KRS 224.1-400, 224.1-405, 224.1-510 to 224.1-532, 224.46-530, and 224.1-450 to 224.1-465; and
The person proposing the environmental covenant has published, through public notice, a notification identifying by legal description and address the property that is being considered for an environmental covenant, the intent to place an environmental covenant on the property, and a list of interest holders of record.
